org.eclipse.ecf.core
Class ContainerFactory

java.lang.Object
  org.eclipse.ecf.core.ContainerFactory
All Implemented Interfaces:
IContainerFactory
public class ContainerFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements IContainerFactory

Factory for creating IContainer instances. This class provides ECF clients an entry point to constructing IContainer instances.

Here is an example use of the ContainerFactory to construct an instance of the 'standalone' container (has no connection to other containers):

IContainer container =
ContainerFactory.getDefault().createContainer("ecf.generic.client");

...further use of container here... For more details on the creation and lifecycle of IContainer instances created via this factory see IContainer.

See Also:
IContainer, IContainerFactory

createContainer

public IContainer createContainer(ContainerTypeDescription description,
                                  java.lang.Object[] parameters)
                           throws ContainerCreateException
Description copied from interface: IContainerFactory
Make IContainer instance. Given a ContainerTypeDescription object, a String [] of argument types, and an Object [] of parameters, this method will

  • lookup the known ContainerDescriptions to find one of matching name
  • if found, will retrieve or create an IContainerInstantiator for that description
  • Call the IContainerInstantiator.createInstance method to return an instance of IContainer

Specified by:
createContainer in interface IContainerFactory
Parameters:
description - the ContainerTypeDescription to use to create the instance
parameters - an Object [] of parameters passed to the createInstance method of the IContainerInstantiator
Returns:
a valid instance of IContainer

ContainerCreateException
